about.body: Located in the Arlo Midtown, Nearly Ninth is an all-day destination for fresh, Italian-inspired fare, coffee and crafted cocktails in a warm, modern setting. Catch a glimpse of our glowing bar through the high street-facing window and feel compelled to enter and stay a while. Move seamlessly through our spaces - bar, lounge and rooftop bar - depending on your mood. During the day, we are the perfect respite from the hustle and bustle of our neighborhood; grab a light bite and catch up with friends (or emails). By night, the lights dim, and we transition to an energized, buzzing bar scene where conversation flows as easily as the expertly calibrated playlist. Hotel guests and local professionals alike will be inspired to return.

need_to_know.body:
Reservations are available 2 weeks in advance. A portion of our bar and dining room is held nightly for walk - ins.
If you are running late, please call us at 212-933-4495

about.body:
Paying homage to the legacy of John W. Campbell, a Jazz Age financier who converted the space to his private office and reception hall in 1923, The Campbell showcases many of the thirteenth century Florentine-inspired design intricacies that upheld its legendary allure, including soaring, 25-foot hand painted ceilings, a grand stone fireplace, Campbell’s personal steel safe, a century-old leaded glass window and original millwork.
Gerber Group’s selection of classic and modern cocktails, that highlight fresh ingredients, wines and locally brewed craft beers, are complemented by a menu of elevated bar fare.

need_to_know.body:
Reservations are available 14 days in advance. A portion of our bar is held nightly for walk - ins.
If you are running late, please call us at 212-297-1781.

about.body: Located at the top of The InterContinental Hotel, boasting a nearly 360-degree view of the Potomac and the Washington skyline, 12 Stories is a sexy, modern addition to The Wharf.

need_to_know.body: Reservations are available 14 days in advance. A portion of our bar and outside area is held nightly for walk-in guests. Parking at The Wharf can be tricky, so please plan in advance so you are not late for the reservation. We will hold the table for a grace period of 30 minutes. We will try to accommodate your request for a patio table but it is not guaranteed.
